<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<html xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"
     xmlns:tal="http://xml.zope.org/namespaces/tal"
     xmlns:metal="http://xml.zope.org/namespaces/metal"
     metal:use-macro="api.community_layout.macros['master']">

  <div metal:fill-slot="content">
    <div class="chparent_wrapper">
      <a id="backto" class="chparent" href="${back_to_calendar_url}">
        <img width="15" height="15" alt="Up to" src="${api.static_url}/images/arrow_up.jpg"/>
        Back to Calendar
      </a>
    </div>

    <h1>Calendar Setup</h1>

    <dl id="calendar_setup">
      <dt><a href="${virtuals_url}">Virtual Calendars</a></dt>
      <dd>
        Virtual Calendars help to organize the calendar events within
        a community.  It may help to think of a virtual calendar as a
        category.  
      </dd>
               
      <dt><a href="${layers_url}">Calendar Layers</a></dt>
      <dd>
        Layers are groupings of virtual calendars. Virtual Calendars are not
        shown on the calendar directly. Instead, they are grouped into layers
        and the layers are shown on the calendar.
      </dd>
    </dl>  

  </div>
</html>
